Jean De Briac https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jean_De_Briac 0 Jean De Briac (born Jean-Frederic Weitler, 15 August 1891 – 18 October 1970) was a French film actor. He appeared in 122 films between 1920 and 1962. He was born in France and died in Los Angeles, California. He immigrated to the United States in 1915.
